description: From Middle French receder, from Latin recedere (“to withdraw; to go back”), from re- + cedere (“to go”).

verbs.description: recede (third-person singular simple present recedes, present participle receding, simple past and past participle receded)

entries.meaning: To move back; to retreat; to withdraw.
examples: All bodies moved circularly have a perpetual endeavour to recede from the center.

entries.meaning: To cede back; to grant or yield again to a former possessor.
